cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.MM 

The paper deals with the problem of multi-target tracking in real-world scenes, which is a common problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes an end-to-end learning approach using recurrent neural networks, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper deals with the problem of state estimation and data association, which are common problems in robotics, and hence it could also belong to cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also proposes a solution that addresses the challenges in a principled way, which falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper presents experiments on both synthetic and real data, which could also make it relevant to cs.MM (Multimedia).
